The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, May 25, 2004 				 Sonia PS for Singh
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, May 24: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh is understood to have chosen Pulok Chatterjee as his personal secretary in the new PMO. 																								Chatterjee, an Uttar Pradesh cadre IAS officer, was Congress president Sonia Gandhis personal secretary during her tenure as Leader of Opposition in the 13th Lok Sabha. 																								Chatterjee had earlier worked with former Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi and also with the Rajiv Gandhi Foundation that Sonia heads. 																								Yesterday, the Prime Minister had appointed T.K. Ayyappankutty Nair, a retired Punjab cadre IAS officer, as his principal secretary.
